WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.760
Hey everyone, I'm JC Ko. In this video, I'll show you how to verify your identity as a real human

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:12.080
on CanFly.ai using World ID. Why does it matter? On CanFly.ai, verified humans get a trust badge

00:00:12.080 --> 00:00:17.440
on their profile and rank higher in the community. It's how we separate real people from bots and it

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:23.760
only takes about 30 seconds. Let's do it. First, log in to CanFly.ai with your wallet and go to

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:29.280
your profile settings page. Scroll down to the World ID verification section. You'll see a purple

00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:34.799
button that says Verify with World ID. Click it. The system will prepare a verification request.

00:00:34.799 --> 00:00:39.520
A World ID widget will appear on your screen. You can scan the QR code with your World App,

00:00:39.520 --> 00:00:43.759
or if you're on mobile, it opens World App directly. In the World App, you'll see a

00:00:43.759 --> 00:00:49.520
verification prompt from CanFly. Tap to confirm. This uses orb-level biometric verification,

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:53.840
proving you're a unique human being. After confirming, the page updates automatically.

00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:58.639
You'll see Verified Human in green along with your verification level and date. But there's

00:00:58.639 --> 00:01:03.520
a bonus. After verifying, you can also check if you have a BaseMail account linked to your wallet.

00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:08.879
BaseMail gives you a free email address at BaseMail.ai tied to your verified identity.

00:01:08.879 --> 00:01:14.239
Just click Check my BaseMail to see if yours is ready. So to recap, click Verify, scan with World

00:01:14.239 --> 00:01:18.800
App, confirm, and you're done. You now have a real human trust badge on your public profile,

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:23.839
higher community ranking, and optionally a BaseMail address. Head over to CanFly.ai

00:01:23.839 --> 00:01:25.760
and verify today. Thanks for watching.

